%++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
\subsection{Food waste}\index{food waste}
\label{sec:ag_mass_Sankey}
%++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Figure~\ref{fig:food_and_ag_material_flow} shows a mass-based, material-flow
Sankey diagram for U.S.\ agriculture. 
Mass-based efficiencies can be calculated for many aspects of the agricultural system.
For example, the efficiency with which crops are converted to edible food
is the ratio 355,880$\times$10$^\text{6}$ pounds of edible food supply 
to 921,590$\times$10$^\text{6}$ pounds of crop production, 
or 38.6\%.

